Comment.Text: Feature extraction is applied. This consists of two simple DSP algorithms extracting power, and averaging over time. These are then converted to feature vectors for the classifiers to use.

Overview Reads a recorded file from the online steering in order to evaluate performance of said run. note: the recorded files go to the folder where the scenario xml is located (${Player_ScenarioDirectory}/).

Feature vectors are classified with classifier of choice (here either SVM or LDA) MATLAB scripting box then takes the probabilities and converts to a confusion matrix which is outputted as a workspace, where it can then be plotted. Alternatively, the OpenViBE box "Matrix display" can be used with small modifications to the matlab scipt.
The CSP spatial filters produced previously are used prior to the feature extraction.
